<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Hypocrite" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Hypocrite</orth> (having <emph>an,</emph> not <emph>a,</emph> before it: <bibl n="shak. mm 5.41" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. V, 41</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.2.64" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 2, 64</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 1.1.122" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 1, 122</bibl>), a dissembler: <bibl n="shak. mm 5.41" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. V, 41</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 1.1.152" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado I, 1, 152</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.2.59" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 2, 59</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.2.59" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 2, 59</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.3.56" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 3, 56</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.2.415" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 2, 415</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.4.42" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 42</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 1.1.122" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 1, 122</bibl>. Used wrongly by Dogberry: <bibl n="shak. ado 5.1.212" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 1, 212</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>